{
  "text": "Before that we must show how to share a secret value x. For that, a dealing party must choose x 1 ← Z 2 and set x 2 ← x ⊕ x 1 and publish enc pk 1 (x 1 ) and enc pk 2 (x 2 ). Next, the opponent obtains its share x j by decrypting and verifies that x j ∈ Z 2 . To show validity of enc pk i (x i ), P i must show that its either encryption of zero or one. The latter can be with corresponding CDSZK proof, which reply a consist of two encryptions. See [CITATION_1] for further details.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "14993660"
